ile-based, and no-op named lock factories used to guard concurrent access to shared resolver resources.\\\",\\nmetadata/org.apache.maven.resolver/maven-resolver-named-locks/1.9.25/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \\\"resources\\\": [\\nmetadata/org.apache.maven/maven-plugin-descriptor/2.1.0/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \\\"resources\\\": [\\nmetadata/io.swagger.core.v3/swagger-annotations/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Swagger Annotations provides Java annotation types for describing OpenAPI metadata on application classes, resources, operations, parameters, schemas, responses, security, and related API elements. It is the annotations-only module used by Swagger Core and compatible tooling to derive OpenAPI definitions from Java code.\\\",\\nmetadata/org.apache.maven.resolver/maven-resolver-named-locks/2.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \\\"resources\\\": [\\nmetadata/org.apache.maven.resolver/maven-resolver-connector-basic/2.0.8/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \\\"resources\\\": [\\nmetadata/org.apache.maven.resolver/maven-resolver-connector-basic/2.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \\\"resources\\\": [\\nmetadata/org.apache.maven.resolver/maven-resolver-connector-basic/1.9.25/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \\\"resources\\\": [\\nmetadata/io.swagger.core.v3/swagger-core-jakarta/2.2.50/reachability-metadata.json:673:  \\\"resources\\\": [\\nmetadata/org.mariadb.jdbc/mariadb-java-client/3.0.6/reachability-metadata.json:30:  \\\"resources\\\": [\\nmetadata/io.awspring.cloud/spring-cloud-aws-autoconfigure/4.0.2/reachability-metadata.json:33:  \\\"resources\\\": [\\nmetadata/org.mariadb.jdbc/mariadb-java-client/3.5.2/reachability-metadata.json:31:  \\\"resources\\\": [\\nmetadata/jakarta.ws.rs/jakarta.ws.rs-api/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Jakarta RESTful Web Services API defines the standard annotations, interfaces, and runtime contracts for building RESTful services and clients in Jakarta EE. This artifact provides only the API types for resources, request and response handling, media negotiation, filters, interceptors, and extension points while implementations are supplied by Jakarta REST runtimes.\\\",\\nmetadata/jakarta.ws.rs/jakarta.ws.rs-api/index.json:24:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Jakarta RESTful Web Services API defines the annotations, interfaces, and core types used to build RESTful web services on the JVM. This artifact provides the API contracts for resources, requests, responses, media types, filters, and client/server extension points rather than a concrete implementation.\\\",\\nmetadata/jakarta.ws.rs/jakarta.ws.rs-api/index.json:38:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Jakarta RESTful Web Services API defines the standard annotations, interfaces, and runtime contracts for building RESTful services and clients in Jakarta EE. This artifact provides only the API types for resources, request and response handling, media negotiation, filters, interceptors, and extension points while implementations are supplied by Jakarta REST runtimes.\\\",\\nmetadata/jakarta.ws.rs/jakarta.ws.rs-api/3.1.0/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \\\"resources\\\": [\\nmetadata/jakarta.ws.rs/jakarta.ws.rs-api/2.1.6/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \\\"resources\\\": [\\nmetadata/jakarta.ws.rs/jakarta.ws.rs-api/3.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \\\"resources\\\": [\\nmetadata/org.glassfish.web/javax.el/2.2.4/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \\\"resources\\\" : [\\nmetadata/com.atomikos/transactions-api/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Atomikos Transactions API defines the public interfaces and configuration contracts for Atomikos-managed distributed transactions, participants, and transactional resources. It also exposes recovery and logging abstractions used to coordinate two-phase commit and crash recovery.\\\",\\nmetadata/ognl/ognl/3.2.21/reachability-metadata.json:163:  \\\"resources\\\" : [\\nmetadata/com.atomikos/atomikos-util/6.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:59:  \\\"resources\\\" : [\\nmetadata/org.glassfi